Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on
medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once the pan is hot, add the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%g}.

Fry until the sausage has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up
as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausage meat.
> When the sausage meat has browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

Meanwhile, trim the @Carrot{1}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways (no need to
peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Once the sausage is browned, stir in the @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet}, @Tomato Passata{1%carton},
@Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g}, carrot and @Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp}
and @Water for the Sauce{150%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring the sauce up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with
#foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the meat is tender and
the sauce has thickened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage meat is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Spaghetti ==

When there are 15 mins of ragu cooking time left, bring a large #saucepan{} of
water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the spaghetti.

When boiling, add the @Spaghetti{180%g} to the water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and
pop back in the pan.

Drizzle with @oil{a drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Ragu Al Forno ==

Remove the ragu from the oven, stir in the @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%g}, cooked
pasta, @Butter{20%g} and half of the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water to
loosen the sauce if you'd like.

Divide your ragu al forno pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian style cheese.

Enjoy!